To gain a further insight into the mechanism underlying quinazoline-induced apoptosis, the temporal expression of several genes involved in TGF-Ξ²1-mediated apoptosis, that is, the ligand TGF-Ξ², its critical receptor TΞ²RII receptor, the intracellular effectors Smad4 and Smad7, and the nuclear factor TIEG1 was evaluated. Since increased TGF-Ξ²1 protein expression is associated with apoptosis (Glassman et al, 2001), we first examined the expression profile of TGF-Ξ²1 in doxazosin-treated prostate cancer cells. A significant increase in TGF-Ξ²1 mRNA expression were detected within the first 12β€‰h of doxazosin treatment (Figure 3B). This mRNA induction for TGF-Ξ² resulted in a significant increase in the levels of active TGF-Ξ²1 protein produced by PC-3 prostate cancer cells (P<0.05). After 24β€‰h of exposure to doxazosin, there was a decline in TGF-Ξ²1 levels to baseline values (Figure 5Figure 5Effect of doxazosin on TGF-Ξ²1 protein secretion by prostate cancer cells. PC-3 prostate cancer cells were treated with doxazosin (25β€‰ΞΌM) for various periods of time as indicated (0β€“24β€‰h). Supernatants were obtained from treated cells and subjected to ELISA as described under β€�Materials and Methodsβ€™. Values represent the mean of three independent experiments performed in duplicateΒ±standard deviation (s.d.).). No changes in the TΞ²RII receptor mRNA expression by PC-3 cells were observed in response to doxazosin (data not shown).
A marked induction in TIEG1 (Figure 3C) and Smad4 (Figure 3D) mRNA levels was observed within 6β€‰h of treatment (65% increase), while there was a transient decrease in Smad7 mRNA expression for 24β€‰h of doxazosin exposure, and it was subsequently followed by an upregulation by 48β€‰h compared to the untreated control PC-3 cells (Figure 3E). Smad4 is an important regulator of TGF-Ξ²1 signalling and apoptosis in a variety of cell lines (Kim et al, 1996; Liu et al, 1997). Considering that Smad4 mRNA is upregulated, we investigated the effect of doxazosin on Smad4 protein levels. As shown in Figure 4C, there was an increase in Smad4 protein expression in response to doxazosin and this elevation was maintained throughout all treatment periods examined (up to 24β€‰h), a pattern that temporally correlates with the mRNA expression profile (Figure 3D).
